Like other swarm optimizers, the location of salps is defined as a D-dimensional vector where D is the dimension of the given problem. Hence, the position of all salps forms a two-dimension matrix called X. It is also supposed that the food source called F in the search space is the foraging target of the swarm. The following equation updates the position of the leader:1X1,j=Fj+c1×c2×ubj-lbj+lbjc3≥0.5Fj-c1×c2×ubj-lbj+lbjc3<0.5,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
