At the same time, seven competitive improved evolutionary algorithms are chosen to participate in this competition; the parameters of all the involved algorithms are listed in Table 2 in detail. The Wilcoxon singed-rank test [62] was utilized with a 0.05 significance level to measure whether there is a statistical significance between CDESSA and other competitors. In the results, “w’’ sign identifies that CDESSA is superior to the competitors, “t” symbol denotes a tie and so there is not a statistically significant difference, and “l” sign signifies CDESSA is inferior to the peer algorithms, and hence CDESSA exhibits the worse performance.Table 2
